\b\fs28 \cf0 Manual triplification\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl360\slmult1\sa240\partightenfactor0

\b0\fs24 \cf0 After this first exploration, we wanted to take a close look at the data contained in less structured resources.\
We try to do that by acting as if we were an archivist wishing to inject biographical information into the Linked Data cloud, in other words, a manual triplification of metadata about Henry.\
We used three different types of resources: an EAC and an EAD files from the State Archives and the national biography about Henry.\
During this triplification process, we took all sentences and tried to extract and translate every single piece of information about Henry into RDF triples (subject, property, object). \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl360\slmult1\sa280\partightenfactor0

\b\fs28 \cf0 Limits\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl360\slmult1\sa240\partightenfactor0

\b0\fs24 \cf0 This triplification process results in several hundred statements, far more complete and detailed than what we got through the RDF triples. \
During this process, we observed several aspects which can lead to loss of information which in turn renders it difficult to deliver a clear and representative description of Henry. \
We have identified three types of limits, which are respectively related to the data, to the triple structure and to the vocabulary.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl360\slmult1\sa240\partightenfactor0

\b\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Think about
